Package com.intellij.openapi.editor

Interface FoldRegion

  • All Superinterfaces:
    RangeMarker, Segment, UserDataHolder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FoldingRegionWindow, FoldRegionImpl

    public interface FoldRegion
extends RangeMarker
    Represents a region of text in the editor which can be folded.
    See Also:
    FoldingModel.addFoldRegion(int, int, String), FoldingModel.getAllFoldRegions()

      • shouldNeverExpand

        boolean shouldNeverExpand()
        If true, this region is always in a collapsed state, setExpanded(boolean) does nothing for it. No marker is displayed in gutter for such a region.
        See Also:
        FoldingModelEx.createFoldRegion(int, int, String, FoldingGroup, boolean)

      • setInnerHighlightersMuted

        default void setInnerHighlightersMuted(boolean value)
        If inner highlighters are muted for a collapsed fold region, there will be no visual indication that region contains certain highlighters inside. By default such indication is added.
        See Also:
        RangeHighlighterEx.isVisibleIfFolded()

      • areInnerHighlightersMuted

        default boolean areInnerHighlightersMuted()
        See Also:
        setInnerHighlightersMuted(boolean)

      • setGutterMarkEnabledForSingleLine

        default void setGutterMarkEnabledForSingleLine(boolean value)
        By default, gutter mark (for collapsing/expanding the region using mouse) is not shown for a folding region, if it's contained within a single document line. This method allows to change this behaviour for given fold region.
        See Also:
        isGutterMarkEnabledForSingleLine(), EditorSettings.setAllowSingleLogicalLineFolding(boolean)

      • isGutterMarkEnabledForSingleLine

        default boolean isGutterMarkEnabledForSingleLine()
        See Also:
        setGutterMarkEnabledForSingleLine(boolean)

      • setPlaceholderText

        default void setPlaceholderText(java.lang.String text)
        Updates region's placeholder text. Should be called inside FoldingModel.runBatchFoldingOperation(Runnable), like any other operations with fold regions.
